\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Decode throughput (tokens/s) across context lengths for all quantization variants (error bars = $\pm 1$ std). At 256--1024 tokens, ordering is non-monotonic with bit-width: Q2\_K $>$ Q4\_K\_M $>$ Q8\_0 $\approx $ Q3\_K\_M $>$ Q6\_K. At ctx=2048, Q3\_K\_M and Q6\_K collapse ($-38\%$ and $-49\%$) while Q4\_K\_M ($+6\%$) and Q2\_K ($-4\%$) stay stable; Q8\_0 declines mildly ($-11\%$).}}{3}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:decode_tps}{{1}{3}{Decode throughput (tokens/s) across context lengths for all quantization variants (error bars = $\pm 1$ std). At 256--1024 tokens, ordering is non-monotonic with bit-width: Q2\_K $>$ Q4\_K\_M $>$ Q8\_0 $\approx $ Q3\_K\_M $>$ Q6\_K. At ctx=2048, Q3\_K\_M and Q6\_K collapse ($-38\%$ and $-49\%$) while Q4\_K\_M ($+6\%$) and Q2\_K ($-4\%$) stay stable; Q8\_0 declines mildly ($-11\%$)}{figure.1}{}}
